References:  https://docs.expo.io/versions/latest/workflow/configuration/ 

You can first update npm with this: 

npm install -g npm (step 1)

npm install -g expo-cli (step 2)

Once this installation is complete, you'll have a new expo command available on your system. 

To start a new project, we can run the expo init command, as follows: 

expo init my-project   (Step 3)

cd into your Project Directory

Run

npm start

Observe the output in your Browser



